          "heading": "1. The Issue",
          "content_markdown": "Whether a District Court's preliminary injunction restoring Lisa Cook \u2014 a Federal Reserve Governor whom the President purported to fire for alleged pre-office mortgage fraud \u2014 to her position pending merits litigation should be stayed. Three sub-questions carry the analysis: **(1)** whether the Federal Reserve Act's \"for cause\" removal provision (12 U.S.C. \u00a7 242) is judicially reviewable at all; **(2)** whether the statute implicitly requires **notice + opportunity to respond** before removal, given its fixed-14-year-term structure; and **(3)** whether federal courts have **equitable authority** to enter interim reinstatement relief against the President's removal of a principal executive officer.\n\nUnderlying the whole case: whether the Federal Reserve \u2014 decided the same day in the companion case *Trump v. Slaughter* \u2014 falls within a **historical-tradition carveout** to that day's newly-announced general rule that principal executive officers must be removable at will."
